Defendant James Robert Held in court with attorney Andrew Joel Golden.  Defendant James Robert Held in custody.  Michael Jerome Lonski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  

AS TO COUNT 2:  On state's motion and by operation of law the Court orders Count 2 DISMISSED.

AS TO COUNT 3:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on state's motion the Court orders Count 3 DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing in Count 1.

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense and defendant. 
 
COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 46 MONTHS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 122 days served.  The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 16 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 2 1/2 YEARS.

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.  The defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENED SUPERVISION:
*Obtain Mental health assessment-if necessary successfully complete follow-up treatment- take prescription medication only as prescribed by physician;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Absolute sobriety with random urine screens and breathalyzer tests;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment;
*Pay all supervision fees;
*Provide DNA sample- pay surcharge;

The Court ordered defendant to pay a fine of $600.00 plus all mandatory costs, penalties, surcharges, including $50.00 ignition interlock surcharge. Court ordered AODA assessment and Driver's Safety Plan; cooperate with any treatment recommended.  Court ordered defendant's driving privileges revoked for a period of 36 months.  Court ordered defendant restricted to operation of vehicles equipped with an ignition interlock device for 36 months.
 
The Court ordered that all financial obligations be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.
Filed;
